# Kernel config symbols the vz (Apple Virtualization.framework) guest kernel
# must have BUILT IN (=y), applied over `make defconfig` via scripts/config,
# then `make olddefconfig`. One symbol per line; blank lines and #-comments
# ignored. The build asserts every symbol is =y in the final .config.
#
# Rationale: vz presents virtio devices over PCI (not MMIO), with no initrd —
# so the guest must drive virtio-PCI itself and mount a raw ext4 root. Refs:
# FR-17.11 (vsock exec), MGIT-11.6 (overlay/fuse), the fr17-vzf-kernel memory.
PCI
PCI_HOST_GENERIC
VIRTIO_MENU
VIRTIO_PCI
VIRTIO_BLK
VIRTIO_CONSOLE
VIRTIO_NET
VSOCKETS
VIRTIO_VSOCKETS
FUSE_FS
VIRTIO_FS
OVERLAY_FS
EXT4_FS
